The three changes in summary:

- **Settings table** reduced to the six entries, section headers removed entirely
- **`NextSelectableSettings`** simplified to a plain wrap since there are no header rows to skip
- **`OpenSettingsMenu`** simplified for the same reason
- **Settings combo** is now B + PLUS (Wii/Classic) or B + START (GC), in both the browser and in-game, using the same edge-triggered two-button detection used previously for the browser combo — one button must be the new press while the other is already held, preventing accidental activation
